Preheat your oven to 180°C. Fill a large #saucepan{} with water and bring to the boil. Trim the @courgette{1} then slice into rounds about 1cm thick. Trim 1cm from the bottom of the @asparagus{100%g} (discard the bottom) then slice down the middle lengthways. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Drain and rinse the @green lentils{1} using a #sieve{}. Halve the @lemon{1}.

Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks and pop on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once golden, remove from your oven and set aside.

In the meantime, heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Add the courgette and season with salt. Leave to cook until charred, ~{5%minutes} each side. Meanwhile, add the asparagus to the boiling water along with 0.25 tsp of salt. Cook for ~{1%minute} then add the @mangetout{80%g} to the pan, cook for ~{1%minute} more. Drain in a #colander{}. Quickly run under cold water until cool then allow to drain fully. Once the courgette is charred, add to a large #bowl{}, set aside to cool.

In a small bowl, mix together the @mayonnaise{1}, @dijon mustard{1/2} and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Squeeze in the lemon juice and add the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing. Add the @water{2%tbsp} for the dressing and season to taste with salt and pepper, mix together.

> TIP: The dressing will be quite thin, but that's fine - it will coat the salad nicely.

Return your now-empty frying pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, add the shallot to the pan. Cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Once soft, stir in the lentils and season with salt and pepper. Cook until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes} stirring occasionally, then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, then roughly tear the leaves into large pieces. Pop them in the large bowl with the courgette. Add the asparagus, mangetout and croutons. Pour over half of the dressing, toss to coat the leaves well, then divide the salad between your #bowls{}.

Spoon the lentils on top of the salad then sprinkle over the @walnuts{20%g} and the remaining hard Italian cheese. Drizzle the rest of dressing all over the top. Enjoy!